results.name: Composite numbers that can be obtained from primes by interchanging the first and last digits.
comment: The primes must contain at least two digits.
example: The composite number 752 is obtained from the prime 257 by interchanging the first and last digits.
xref: The corresponding primes are A076056. Cf. A002808, A179826.
results.author: _Parthasarathy Nambi_, Aug 06 2010
